{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 18502, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "Suzaku", "body": "Dar'Khan, an undead high elf, is the antagonist of The Sunwell Trilogy manga series. http://www.wowwiki.com/Dar'khan", "date": "2006-12-29T16:36:13-06:00", "rating": 67, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Indeed, he appears in all 3 novels but he is not dressed like a mage in the manga series, but more like a ranger. Nontheless, he was said to have been vaporized by Anveena in the last book of the trilogy, but still apears in WoW, though there are no stories related to hisressurection.", "creationdate": "2008-07-22T13:39:51-05:00", "id": 40463, "rating": 3, "commentid": 18502, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "135596", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "An interesting bit of trivia here.   Dar'Khan was killed by Anveena, but is now back. The building in which he is found (Tower of the Damned) bears a striking resemblance to the Altar of Darkness in Undercity's War Quarter; for those who didn't know, the Altar of Darkness was a building in Warcraft III Undead constructed to revive dead heroes.   Gotta love Blizz's little references. :D", "creationdate": "2009-03-05T21:33:34-06:00", "id": 83924, "rating": 35, "commentid": 18502, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Draol", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Its quite possible he's a lich of some sort. Since destroying their bodies completely wont stop them. As long as they have their phylactory hidden away safe and unharmed they can always come back", "creationdate": "2012-11-03T12:42:26-05:00", "id": 594752, "rating": 1, "commentid": 18502, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Tenjen", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This is the second time Dar'Khan came back from complete death. The first, he was consumed by fire in the Sunwell Trilogy but showed up again when Kalec and Anveena reached the Ghostlands. So it's not unprecedented.", "creationdate": "2012-12-01T04:42:20-06:00", "id": 605817, "rating": 1, "commentid": 18502, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Reignac", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "He should have been killed by Arthas in a book... But his leggins are too faboulous!", "creationdate": "2016-02-23T09:22:39-06:00", "id": 931305, "rating": 0, "commentid": 18502, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Tilpion", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 107210, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Retribution", "body": "You can beat him two ways.\r\n\r\nFirst, you can pull the Necromancers near him one at a time with a ranged attack, as long as you stay out of his aggro range, then solo him in the room which gives you a lot more space to move...\r\n\r\n Or you can apparantly pull him out of the room on his own with the same method and beat him upstairs.", "date": "2007-06-19T13:37:41-05:00", "rating": 19, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "The second strategy is very risky as he has a mass fear attack and CAN resist the effects of the weapons you get to silence him. The upstairs mobs also respawn VERY fast, within a few minutes, so that mass fear can cause a great many problems.  I advise the use of pulling the surrounding mobs, this can be done with nearly every class including paladins as they are vulnerable to Exorcism, which has a casting range farther than most paladin spells, due to being undead.", "creationdate": "2007-06-30T04:12:53-05:00", "id": 10650, "rating": 15, "commentid": 107210, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "46881", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "That's a lie.  The mobs upstair does not respawn quickly. The only possibility of them respawning quickly is if there is like 20 people just at Death Holme, trying to kill the other mobs which will force them to respawn due to the rule of killing 1 makes another one somewhere else to respawn.  The best tactic to kill Dar'Khan is to use ranged to pull him. He will come alone and he dies easily. Solo'd it as a 21 Shaman even just to see how easy it was.", "creationdate": "2007-09-26T19:29:20-05:00", "id": 312211, "rating": -2, "commentid": 107210, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "89242", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Soloing as a 22 Shadow Priest  http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gbodwauQYJQ", "creationdate": "2009-04-11T06:20:40-05:00", "id": 90559, "rating": 5, "commentid": 107210, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "78037", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 2, "id": 115056, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "9857", "body": "You should also note that the Blood Elf racial \"Mana Tap\" can be used to pull the surrounding mobs.", "date": "2007-07-03T14:12:48-05:00", "rating": 17, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Just completed the quest for his head today.  Druid pulled Dar'Khan alone up the stairs and my 23 pally wailed on him for a while.  I am a tiny bit twinked as a result of helping out a newbie who's brother, a 70, was going to run him through SFK later, which i ended up tagging along for.  Plus, a good one-handed sword had dropped for me out of the blue in Hillsbrad.  Anyway, I didn't do much beyond Seal of Command, attack, Judgement, and throw in a Hammer of Justice before Judgement when i could.  I had a couple of buffs and a strength scroll on me which helped.  Druid healed, he got feared tw", "creationdate": "2007-07-03T14:12:49-05:00", "id": 307510, "rating": 7, "commentid": 115056, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "65237", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Unfortunately Mana Tap ability was removed. No easy ranged pulls for Blood Elf paladins any more...", "creationdate": "2008-10-27T08:04:50-05:00", "id": 52934, "rating": 3, "commentid": 115056, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "236108", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You can pull the undead minions with Exorcism which will also pull the humanoid caster.", "creationdate": "2008-12-13T20:17:30-06:00", "id": 64497, "rating": 2, "commentid": 115056, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "197261", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "and also with hand of reckoning", "creationdate": "2009-08-14T10:38:02-05:00", "id": 116069, "rating": 1, "commentid": 115056, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "346511", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 3, "id": 189839, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "42092", "body": "Although not easy, this guy is soloable by hunters. As a lvl 20 hunter and after a couple of attempts I managed to get him down. First off clear the bottom and middle room (do it quick, as you'll need the time before respawns come). Just tank with the pet and mend pet should keep pet up. At a point (for me it was around 50% health) he began to fear the pet. He still attacked it though, but pet couldnt generate aggro so after a while he went for me. Just kite him around in the middle room, keeping serpent sting on him and use immolation trap whenever off CD, and he should go down before respawns.", "date": "2007-11-23T07:26:45-06:00", "rating": 10, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 4, "id": 205680, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Arathanar", "body": "Warlocks can solo this somewhat well if they know the class somewhat well, and have 4+ soulshards on hand. After clearing his guards/luckily pulling him alone, open the fight with your Voidwalker (Succubi don't work for this strategy), have him use Torment 2-3 times. Then use your orb/sword. If you pull aggro or if your Voidwalker is below 1/3 HP, Sacrifice and Re-summon your Voidwalker. Do this right after using the item, because the silence effect will prevent Dar'khan from fearing you, which will interrupt the summon. Beyond that, tank and spank, Sacrificing/Re-summoning at low HP.", "date": "2007-12-22T16:49:39-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "It's much easier as a warlock to DoT kite him. Just get him without his adds and kite him around the room, reapplying one dot or the other frequently enough that he doesn't evade back. Takes about a minute or two max.", "creationdate": "2008-04-21T01:49:42-05:00", "id": 332840, "rating": 0, "commentid": 205680, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Cryptorchild", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 5, "id": 218097, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Annai", "body": "Not sure if this has been changed, but I was in a 5-man and it wasn't terribly easy even with 5, nevermind solo'ing. Not sure of group composition, though. Might've had a few lower levels along. The respawn inside the building was *very* fast. Hard to imagine not having re-pops if trying to do this alone.", "date": "2008-01-14T08:21:55-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 222020, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "67278", "body": "Just soloed him as a 20 warlock.  Pulled him without pulling the two mobs on his sides and just kited him with corruption and CoA.  Had  my voidwalker on him but it didnt do much.  I had a respawn at like 8% but was able to finish  him and crap the quest item.", "date": "2008-01-22T00:18:00-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 228139, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "122648", "body": "i did him whit 3ppl  me lvl19 rogue \r\nlvl19 druid (heal)\r\nHunter lvl20 and pet lvl19 (tank)", "date": "2008-02-02T04:27:53-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 8, "id": 236413, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "105251", "body": "I just soloed him as a level 20 paladin. My gear was quite decent, but not superb. I was also heavily buffed via scrolls and the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=23444]Goldenmist Special Brew[/url], but it really did seem too easy.  Considering the nature of the quest (5-man, level 21 elite), it makes me wonder if they've nerfed this mob recently. \n\nThe advice to pull the caster mobs up into the hallway first, with Mana Tap, worked perfectly. It definitely makes it much easier if you can take this guy alone in the room. I had to jump up onto the stone railing to reach them, but that's not difficult.\n\nIt was a relatively lengthy fight. I saved Hammer of Justice for his fears. Mana Tapped every time it came up. Bubbled once, and had to use Lay on Hands. I also used one of the Coarse Stone Statues from Jewel Crafting. He doesn't hit very hard at all, and his casts are quite slow. It's very easy to heal in this fight - pushback is barely a problem.\n\nAnd now that I think about it, I completely forgot to use the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=22783]Sunwell Blade[/url], or the Scourgebane [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=22779]Draught[/url]/[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=22778]Infusion[/url]. Both would have also helped.", "date": "2008-02-15T02:13:32-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-02-15T02:20:29-06:00", 1, "105251"]}
