{"commentv2": 1, "number": 12, "id": 280604, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "42639", "body": "If you're doing this at Lvl 20 or so, it might not be a bad idea to bring a Priest if you can find one. A L20 Priest should've just learned Fear Ward and will get a chance to use it situationally here for the first time. Makes the encounter a lot easier.", "date": "2008-05-01T18:56:39-05:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 13, "id": 312692, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "96362", "body": "omg found on my nearly forgotten level 21 warlock the head of Dar'Khan Darthir. lol I forgot to turn it in. I remember now at level 17 I paired up with a level 60 something Orc Mage and fallowed through the quest with ease, but for some retarded reason I never turned Dar'Khan's head in that is till just now! I took that staff it's real nice.", "date": "2008-06-25T11:04:24-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
