{"commentv2": 1, "number": 15, "id": 332476, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Holydeathknight", "body": "Well this is nothing to do with the quest but i think he should be a higher level since he was fighting off slyvanas And dragon raid boss's all Imo.", "date": "2008-07-21T22:25:11-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 16, "id": 335439, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "135484", "body": "This is a moderately hard guy to defeat but is doable with a dps tank and a good healer. Me and a friend pulled this off as a 20 rogue and a 20 pally. Much easier with a group of 5 but are in short supply in the Ghostlands.", "date": "2008-07-24T22:15:41-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 17, "id": 341218, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "wye43", "body": "As of 2.4.3 patch, he can be pulled alone directly, don't bother with the 4 adds.\n\nClear the bottom level of the temple before pulling, so you can kite him in a circle if needed.\n\nWhen he starts casting [b]Shadow Bolt[/b], just cut a corner and bandage. Make sure you interrupt his [b]Corruption[/b], or you can't bandage.\n\nDon't fight near his original spot, or you have a high chance to get the adds on you, especially during his [b]Fear[/b].\n\nThat being sad, he can relatively easy be 2-maned or even soloed. I just killed him with a party of 19 hunter and 20 rogue. Oh, and yeah, we did it without using the quest item on him, dumb us forgot to use it :), I guess its even easier with the quest item.\n\nNo way you need 5-man as the quest suggests, unless you want to storm the place and handle tons of adds :P", "date": "2008-07-31T07:39:40-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-07-31T09:49:32-05:00", 2, "wye43"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 18, "id": 362159, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "111622", "body": "[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=26046]Anveena[/url] plays a huge part in the history of this forgotten character, read on more about him from her side as he captures Anveena and tries to claim the Sunwell on his own.\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.wowwiki.com/Anveena]Anveena's History, and Dar'Khan Drathir's capturing of her.[/url]", "date": "2008-08-26T01:49:06-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 19, "id": 413319, "nreplies": 8, "sticky": 0, "user": "200795", "body": "This guy is the main villain in a trilogy, seemingly immortal, commanding a part of the Scourge, with seemingly unlimited power.\nIt took the combined power of the Sunwell itself, Tyrygosa and her mate Kalecgos to finally defeat (destroy?) him.\n\nAnd here he is, as a level 21 elite...\n\n_\n\nOf course there are gameplay factors to take into account (\"have\" to be in a starting-zone, Blood Elf lore etc) but seeing such a badguy being reduces to this? It's like creating a level 15 version of Ragnaros!\n\nAnyway, for making this comment relatively useful in any way.. he was \"easily\" (edit) duo:d by a 16 paladin (me) and a 20 hunter. healing the pet as long as possible, and using the 500 dmg silencing sword", "date": "2008-10-20T10:53:47-05:00", "rating": 27, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "\"he was \"easily\" [i][b]soloed[/b][/i] by a [i]16 paladin (me) and a 20 hunter[/i]\"  I don't think that word means what you think it means.", "creationdate": "2008-12-20T19:58:42-06:00", "id": 66470, "rating": 38, "commentid": 413319, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "197261", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Habit of saying soloed when doing something with less people than required i guess.  Duo:ed.. :>", "creationdate": "2008-12-21T18:14:11-06:00", "id": 373316, "rating": 2, "commentid": 413319, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "200795", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Well, lore signifigance/power =/= status in game. Altough it usually correlates, but for example Zalazane is supposedly one bad-ass mofo (just read up on him in [s]Wikipedia[/s] Wowwiki), yet he's a level 10 non-elite killed with little effort by level 8 characters.  And of course more infamously, recently that Anub'arak, a fan-favourite and former king of the Nerubians, is a mere 5 man dungeon boss loot-pinata.", "creationdate": "2009-04-23T04:29:10-05:00", "id": 93303, "rating": 3, "commentid": 413319, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Nordigo", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "@korvhuve--well, usually, undead aren't in as good shape after repeated resurrections. Either that or Dar'khan's being pwned by Angry Wee Sunwell Woman irritated Arthas so much that he nerfed him to the ground.", "creationdate": "2012-09-21T19:59:37-05:00", "id": 573215, "rating": 1, "commentid": 413319, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "MiltiadesBooga", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Its quite possible he's a lich of some sort. Since destroying their bodies completely wont stop them. As long as they have their phylactory hidden away safe and unharmed they can always come back", "creationdate": "2012-11-03T12:43:49-05:00", "id": 594753, "rating": 2, "commentid": 413319, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Tenjen", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-06-06T16:32:17-05:00", 2, "200795"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 20, "id": 537671, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "100748", "body": "The quest log is misleading, theres no way this is a level 21 5 man. Tried soloing him as a lvl 19 Ret Pally, he feared me into the reaspawned adds upstairs after I got him to about  one third health remaining and I died. Leveled later, trained Exorcism and Flash of Light etc. and grouped with a well geared level 17 hunter. I tanked him with the Sunwell Blade and the Reforged Crest shield, for any pally it shouldnt be difficult to keep threat with RF and keep yourself healed, Lay On Hands is good for emergencies if you nearly hit 0. The adds in his room respawned mid-fight, but the hunter and his pet didn't take long in dealing with them. He did fear us upstairs and we had to deal with those adds as well, his fear is very difficult to interrupt as the blade/orb use CAN be resisted and his fear is a very quick cast. I wouldn't recommend anybody soloing this until at least level 23, although it would probably be easy enough for 2 lower levels of any class; if a pally isn't tanking you probably won't get very far if one of you isn't a healer however.", "date": "2008-12-30T10:04:54-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 21, "id": 549131, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Cydelix", "body": "Soloed on my level 21 paladin.\r\nPretty good gear, including http://www.wowhead.com/?item=44099 \r\n\r\nWas buffed with:\r\nhttp://www.wowhead.com/?item=22779\r\nhttp://www.wowhead.com/?item=22778\r\n\r\nCleared the room by pulling with Exorcism.\r\n\r\nStarted out with using http://www.wowhead.com/?item=22783 and then switched back to my normal weapon which had more DPS. Kept Exorcism on cooldown. Hammer of Justice, followed by Judgement of Light.\r\n\r\nUsed line of sight to get out of his Shadowbolt and Corruption.\r\n\r\nUsed Arcane Torrent if I wouldn't make it in time going line of sight.\r\n\r\nIf you take damage, heal the second you go out of line of sight.\r\nIf needed, use Healing Pot. Lay on Hands when low hp and divine protection. (Hand of Protection doesn't help)\r\n\r\nHope it helps.", "date": "2009-01-06T01:42:48-06:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
