{"commentv2": 1, "number": 23, "id": 623228, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "329285", "body": "i soloed him as a 20 pally, and found it easy with mediocre gear. i thought i need to kill him for http://www.wowhead.com/?item=24226. as a pally, all you need to do is keep up the lvl 20 AOE, use judgement of wisdom when you are at low mana, and keep one of your judgements up at all times. when at low health, bubble heal, or lay hands. this was easy if i kept myself healthy. i didnt even have the quest to kill him, and no scourgebane potions. i think he may have been seriously nerfed recently.", "date": "2009-02-25T16:58:21-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "That, or due to the recent pally buffs =)", "creationdate": "2009-05-21T02:50:29-05:00", "id": 99218, "rating": 2, "commentid": 623228, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "175212", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-02-25T17:00:10-06:00", 1, "329285"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 24, "id": 624711, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "293980", "body": "soloed him at lvl 24, as a holy priest, didnt use the orb to slience him to or clear the bottom room. I didnt see any way to clear it wothout pulling him, but his second fear sent me down an to both sides pulling all of the mobs down there aswell. I managed to survive all of them by keeping shield and renew up the whole time, and wanding him down to save mana. Took about 4-5 minutes to down him, and had to clean up the rest of the mobs after.", "date": "2009-02-26T23:16:35-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 25, "id": 632174, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Psyblade1st", "body": "Random experience I had with Dar'Khan: I was running through the Ghostlands for the exporation achievement (Alliance Paladin, 70 at that time) and I thought of passing by Dar'Khan.\r\n\r\nI rode past a small group of Blood elves, (level 17, 16 and 14, if I recall correctly) who were talking between themselves in Orcish (no doubt discussing strategies to beat this guy). I passed by (Vashj being a PvP server and two of them backed off: Their PvP flags were up for a reason. I ignored them and went in before Dar'Khan. Bored as I was, I didn't feel the urge to gank anyone, so I waited until the third one, 16 Blood Elf mage ran in. The others fell in soon, their PvP flags still up, but I pointed at them, and then pointed at him.\r\n\r\nThe mage probably felt I was of good intentions, so she pulled up a fireball and blasted it at Dar'Khan. Once he was tapped, I moved in, crushing him with a Crusader Strike on the spot. The adds came in (possibly aggroed by one of the three questers), but I jumped on them, and hit my Divine Storm.\r\n\r\nOne of them (Flagged) died instantly, so I sticked by until he came back. He rezzed and looted Dar'Khan's corpse. I then /begged them (wanting them to keep my presence secret from any bloodthirsty 80 near Silvermoon, and they just /nod and /thanks.\r\n\r\nIt was rather fun...", "date": "2009-03-05T12:13:45-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Ghostlands isn't a place you can get flagged at, even on a PvP server. So, either BS or them elves are stupid. Or mayhap they changed the rules.", "creationdate": "2009-06-02T18:14:40-05:00", "id": 409080, "rating": 0, "commentid": 632174, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "283918", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You are flagged after leaving BGs even on PvE servers.  If they had just left WSG they would have been flagged for 5min.", "creationdate": "2009-09-17T20:10:15-05:00", "id": 122513, "rating": 2, "commentid": 632174, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "108118", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 26, "id": 634652, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "309613", "body": "From Wowwiki.com:\r\nDar'Khan Drathir was a member of the Convocation of Silvermoon during the Second War. When warned by Alleria Windrunner of the potential threat of an alliance between the Horde and the Amani forest trolls under Zul'jin, Dar'Khan scoffed and believed that they would not be able to get past the Runestones that protected the borders of Eversong Woods.\r\n\r\nAs a magister of Quel'Thalas, Dar'Khan used the Sunwell to help construct the cities, shape the land, and attain whatever the high elves desired. He was also a friend of future Regent Lord Lor'themar Theron. Lack of recognition for his part in these glorious deeds, coupled with his own egotistical nature, pushed him down a dark path and he began to secretly develop his own magics, as well as an obsession with the Sunwell. Frustrated by a lack of progress, Dar'Khan was elated when Prince Arthas reached out to aid him, and pledged his loyalty to the despoiler of Lordaeron. \r\n\r\nManipulated and strengthened by his \"Blessed Lord\", it was his friendship with Lor'themar that allowed Dar'Khan to help Arthas and his army slip through the Quel'Thalassian defenses, slaughtering his own comrades in the process, all the while believing that Arthas was helping him to fulfill his desire for the Sunwell's power. While he battled his fellow magi for control of the Sunwell, Arthas used it to revive Kel'Thuzad, destroying it in the process. \r\n\r\nAshamed of his failure and unaware of Arthas' role in the destruction, Dar'Khan was sent to track down where the remaining magic had gone. \r\n\r\nThe Sunwell Trilogy \r\nDar'khan assaulting Quel'Thalas.Following years of fruitless searching he finally neared his goal, detecting the Sunwell's presence near a peasant girl named Anveena Teague, who had also drawn attention from members of the Blue Dragonflight. Dar'Khan, now skilled in necromancy and commanding Scourge forces, attempted to capture her and ascertain the power's whereabouts. After failed attempts at her home and again in Tarren Mill, he finally came to the realization that she was, in fact, an Avatar of the Sunwell's power in humanoid form. Kidnapping her in Alterac Mountains and spiriting her to the ruined lands of Quel'Thalas, now known as the Ghostlands, he confronted her with the truth of her existence. \r\n\r\n \r\nDar'khan is destroyed.Dar'Khan then attempted to cast a spell which would allow him to absorb the energies from her, however with the aid of her allies, Anveena manifested the Sunwell's power and wielded it against him. More lich than a living being, he made a final desperate attempt to drain the energy from her directly, but was unable to withstand its brilliance and was burned away.", "date": "2009-03-07T16:30:20-06:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I'm sure all of that is true, and it's very fascinating, which is why I laugh when I read \"Arthas: Rise of the Lich King,\" which says that not only was Dar'Khan present when Arthas defiled the sunwell, but he was also killed by Arthas then as well.  The version from the Sunwell Trilogy is far more interesting, though.", "creationdate": "2011-01-13T18:05:22-06:00", "id": 214982, "rating": 2, "commentid": 634652, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Goldsmith129", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Also has a lot more of Dar'Khan fanboy-squeeing at Arthas. roflmao", "creationdate": "2012-09-17T00:05:02-05:00", "id": 571959, "rating": 0, "commentid": 634652, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "MiltiadesBooga", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
