{"commentv2": 1, "number": 43, "id": 1104219, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "alicerozen", "body": "Level 22 priest. Run in circles around his rooms, kiting him, keep dots and holy fire on him. Heal as necessary. You might need to use a mana potion and your racials handy.", "date": "2010-08-20T06:23:00-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 44, "id": 1108321, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Ramesh256", "body": "So I was summoned to the Ghostlands by an Alliance raid with my level 20 Night Elf druid. I thought it would be fun to try to kill Dar'Khan, so I came to his lair. I killed both Necromancers, then opened with a Starfire (~500 crit) and started spamming Wrath (~210 each, 300+ on crits). My druid had about 1100 health, so I used Wrath a number of times before I was down to low health. I used a Healing Touch, and by this time he was down to about 800 health, so I viciously nuked him with Wrath and killed him. The whole process took about 35 seconds. Amazingly, he didn't use Fear during the whole encounter. This was very easy, no need to run around like some others do.\r\n\r\nI used standard blue gear with a level 40 green hat, all enchanted with +spell power and +spell crit (explains my ridiculous DPS at this level).", "date": "2010-08-26T11:21:54-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 45, "id": 1114105, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "352798", "body": "Me as a lvl 1 paladin and a friend as a lvl 1 rogue managed to 2 man him with the right enchants and buffs. It took forever though, since his HP is a lot higher than most other lvl ~20 elites + he even put corruption on me while the rogue had agro. Fear is a *!@#$ too.\r\n\r\nCheck the fight below:\r\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3kPomwqg2L4", "date": "2010-09-05T13:13:39-05:00", "rating": 25, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I attenpted to solo him with my lvl 20 arms warrior 4 times with no luck. I get him down to about 250, he casts that \"fear\" spell on me (you'll get immobilized and everything turns sideways) and -The End-. The \"Scourgebane Draught\" potion you get for collecting \"rotting hearts\" does some extra damage; And, as stated above, the Sunwell blade or orb you get earlier in the questline does not silence his \"fear\" spell, and the blade only has 10.? dps. I can solo lvl 25's with ease and 22 Elites, this guys tougher than he looks.", "creationdate": "2013-04-03T13:11:23-05:00", "id": 648054, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1114105, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "1018586", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 46, "id": 1156411, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "92594", "body": "I solo'd this quest today as lvl 22 Frost Mage. No heirloom items and quest greens only. I had Elixir of Minor Fortitude, Bobbing Apple, and Blood Thistle for buffs. Once you get inside Dar' Khans dungeon tomb the trick is to take out all the mobs quickly. There is 1 patrol, 4 summoning casters, and Dar' Khan himself. \r\n\r\nOnce you kill the patrol shade, quickly kill each summoner, and their minions on both sides of the second level. When you reach the room with Dar' Khan move to the edges of the door way on either side to kill each of the remaining two summoners. They will not aggro Dar' Khan. However, trying to pull Dar' Khan alone will aggro both summoners/minions onto you. \r\n\r\nRest up quickly to ensure the respawns will not cause you problems so it's just you and Dar' Khan. Make sure your Sunwell Blade is armed. Throw a couple of Frostbolts and counterspell him if he tries to Shadowbolt you. Once he is in range use your Sunwell Blade for the 500+ dmg/Silence effect over 5 secs. If you fail to use this blade it will more than likely lead to your death.\r\n\r\nHere is where the skill comes into play. Freeze with your Water Elemental or use your own Nova. Kite him up and down the stairwells in a rectangular pattern. Anytime he stops to cast, snare with Frostbolt, and get off a Fireblast. If he is about to cast  line of site him. Blink to keep your distance but do not get to far ahead, or he will circle the other way and come from behind. He will focus alot of his corruptions and fear on your Elemental, but it's better him than you. Expect to take a corruption and a fear every now in then. It's hard to use your elementals freeze in this situation, but use it whenever you can while your Nova is on cooldown. Cone of Cold is a very useful snare here too. I'm an herbalist so Life Blood in addition to First Aid saved me as well. \r\n\r\nA player in Heirloom items, and green/blue grafted or purchased gear would be able to do this without even kiting. However, if your are not in this situation and have good movement skills you can pull this strategy off. By good movement skills I simply mean you move with your mouse NOT WASD. The spell dmg potion you receive for 10x Spinal Dust would help tremendously as well. This strategy is for Frost Mages with the new talent trees implemented for Cataclysm. As a wise Mage once told me 4 years ago...\"If you can snare it, you can kill it\". Good luck getting the rare quest staff on your own, and thanks for reading my post.\r\n\r\nPlease Note: Excuse my post that turned into a book, and also my horrible punctuation/grammar. I'm a wow player not an English Major. I hope this info can help any class who has a pet and is capable of kiting. Warocks and Hunters at lvl 22 have it far easier than a Mage though.", "date": "2010-10-29T21:55:15-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
