{"commentv2": 1, "number": 48, "id": 1358374, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "755535", "body": "I just can't kill him! (Solo) \r\nI needed a healer for my lvl25 prot. Warrior", "date": "2011-03-05T14:34:49-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I managed to solo him as a warrior (level 22).  It was not easy and more than once did I want to put a fist through my monitor.    At first, I did two or three pulls as prot and found that I could not do near enough damage to him before I died so I respecced Fury (3/3 Blood Craze is crucial) for Bloodthirst healing.  While it is a small heal, Bloodthrist and Blood Craze gave me just enough self-healing to at least let me live a bit longer.  The real trick is honestly just pure luck.  If he gets even one fear off, you will more than likely die.  A second fear cast is fatal.  When I killed him a", "creationdate": "2011-03-05T14:34:50-06:00", "id": 488068, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1358374, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Xiahoufig", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 49, "id": 1561017, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "MASDERCHEEF", "body": "Patch 4.2-- Just took my first attempt at soloing Dar'Khan. I made two fatal mistakes: 1, going in without any mana potions. This is a big one, seeing as I'm a level 21 Pally. (Prot, if that matters). Mistake number two was letting myself get feared away from the chamber he started in. Normally, there are two cultists and two skeletons next to him. When you get feared, you may be taken out of the chamber where he spawns. MAKE SURE YOU RUN BACK DOWN. You may pick up one or two adds on your first Fear, but as long as you can make it back to the bottom room you should be good. I didn't run back, and picked up half of the mobs in the building, leading to my demise.", "date": "2011-11-02T16:31:59-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 50, "id": 1573642, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Belegalas", "body": "Solo'd him as a level 19 rogue.\r\nHad to use Evasion but the strat is simple. \r\nKill all the npcs upstairs and kill the nps around him by using your bow to pull. \r\nAfterwards make sure you've got some bandages and use Recuperate alot! \r\nAmbush him whatever, build up your combo points and then when he casts an induction Line of Sight him. Make sure you're hitting Recuperate everytime it's up, and don't use combo points for Eviscerate. When you're LoSing him Recuperate will do its job, and if you're in dire need pop a bandage and heal while he's trying to get off an induction while you're sitting behind a wall. Repeat everytime he pops those inductions...you don't want to get hit by them. \r\n\r\nYou should be okay considering Recuperate does its job and you're smacking him everytime he runs towards you.", "date": "2011-11-16T14:54:07-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
