{"commentv2": 1, "number": 53, "id": 2284767, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "MissSea", "body": "Noone has mentioned the cool \"nod\" Blizz gave to Terry Goodkind's Sword of Truth series! Darken Rahl is the main antagonist for a bit of the series, and it's a WONDERFUL read! The series \"Legend of the Seeker\" is also based on this series -- and if you don't mind Sam Raimi-camp (ala Xena and Hercules) -- the show is pretty good too. :D", "date": "2015-12-06T18:01:28-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Don't mean to reply to something so old but you do know that the character Dar'khan is older the sword of truth series right?", "creationdate": "2020-04-05T21:26:13-05:00", "id": 1361492, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2284767, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "LeBob", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 54, "id": 2349991, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "majesticPhaZon", "body": "This quest is one of the hardest ones I've done so far, and since no one was willing to help me, I decided to solo it as a Lvl 20 Demonology warlock.\nI spent so much time on that quest and rage quit SO MUCH before I actually managed to do it.\nSo here's my strategy.\nPrime minions to use: Imp and VW.\nPrime spells to use: Soulfire, Corruption, Hand of Gul'dan, Fear, Drain Life, Create Healthstone, Dark Regeneration (if possible), Soulstone, and Life Tap\n\nStep by step walkthrough:\n\n1: Use your VW. Kill all mobs on the outer ring of the tower. (both pairs of Eye of Dar'khan and anything that wanders around)\n\n2: Enter the tower. Go one path and kill the mobs on that side. Use Fear if necessary.\n\n3: Now go to the other side and kill the mobs there. If anything wanders around and tries to kill you, just kill it back. Make sure you've destroyed the wandering Wailer and the Eye of Dar'khan before you proceed to Step 4.\n\n4: This is the hard part. Switch to your imp and make sure you can actually see the necromancer or its pet in the circular room where Dar'khan is standing. Then target it and kill it. Be absolutely CERTAIN your imp will not aggro anyone else, ESPECIALLY Dar'khan. Recommendation is to start on the left side outside of the dome and kill the mobs on the right side of the room.\n\n5: Repeat #4, except on the other side of the room. This will be a tad trickier.\n\n6: Now this is the fun part. Switch back to your VW, cast Dark Regeneration, trigger Soulstone, and (sort of) Leeroy into the room. Dar'Khan is immune to your Fear spell, so don't mind wasting mana on it. I was a blood elf while I was doing this, so I used my racial passive Arcane Torrent ability to stop him from casting [i]his[/i] Fear. If you exit the room while you are Feared, make sure you get close enough to Dar'Khan as possible when it's done. If your VW dies, resummon it immediately. If you're low on mana (which happens a LOT), use Life Tap, but not so much that you're almost at the point of dying. If you die, make sure Dar'khan's returned back to the circular room before using your Soulstone for resurrection. Use your Healthstone if you've got the time.\n\n7: If you beat him, congrats! Take his head and go to Magister Keandris. He'll send you to Lor'themar Theron and you'll be dubbed a hero of the sin'dorei. (If you're not a blood elf, you'll become their best friend.)\n\n[i]P.S. The rewards are worth it![/i]", "date": "2016-07-10T18:47:49-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2016-07-15T08:11:07-05:00", 4, "majesticPhaZon"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 55, "id": 2863136, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "MintySinty", "body": "Check out Darahir in the Black Market in Northrend Dalaran. \r\nI highly doubt Dar'khan is gone for good. \r\nOdd, too, that the void elves were noted to have been using Dar'khan's research to understand the Void.", "date": "2018-12-31T01:35:47-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 56, "id": 3250810, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "diaskeaus", "body": "Best experience I\u2019ve ever had in WoW, soloing this guy in Chromie Time.\r\n\r\nI used a Windwalker Monk, level 31.\r\n\r\nFirst I cleared all of the enemies in the tower. They spawn slowly so if you kill all of them quickly you will have a few minutes to work on the boss.\r\n\r\nThen I set my spirit teleport on the other side of the tower. \r\n\r\nFinally, activate your three elemental form CD, and then start wailing on Dar\u2019Khan. Pop defensive and absorb CDs, and when your health is getting low activate your teleport to give you time to Revitalize.\r\n\r\nHe is a caster so you can hug walls to avoid spells. \r\n\r\nKeep hitting him until your health is getting low and then use your rolls/spins to quickly move around tower so your can restore health.\r\n\r\nFinally, when he gets under your max health (for me that was around 4K) you can just Touch of Death him and he goes down. \r\n\r\nBreathe out!\r\n\r\nProbably even a more amazing experience at level 49!", "date": "2020-11-19T02:41:41-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}